  <a href="#1" id="1">
   THE STORY OF SPIERS
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Ronald I. Spiers, a veteran U.S. diplomat, will be the new undersecretary-general for General Assembly affairs, the top-ranking American post at the world body, U.N. officials said on July 31, 1989.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Spiers has been a member of the U.S. delegation to the United Nations; was director of political affairs for the U.S. Spiers, 64, is a career foreign service officer, most recently serving as undersecretary of state for management since 1983.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Spiers was ambassador to Pakistan from 1981-83 and has served as ambassador to the Bahamas and Turkey.
  </a>
